        <name>18.3.1.2 T Features on graph</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In each of these figures, what are the features at \(A\) and \(B\)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;figure class="HELM_figure"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/18.3%20Surface%202.svg" alt="Plot of a 3 dimensional surface" width="463" height="345" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;\(A\) is a: [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;\(B\) is a: [[input:ans2]]&amp;nbsp;[[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;figure class="HELM_figure"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/18.3%20Surface%203.svg" alt="Plot of a 3 dimensional surface" width="449" height="345" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;\(A\) is a: [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;\(B\) is a: [[input:ans4]]&amp;nbsp;[[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;From feature \(A\), depending on the direction we move in we can either gain or loose height. Hence, \(A\) is a &lt;b&gt;saddle point&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;From feature \(B\), no matter what direction we move in we always gain height. Hence, \(B\) is a &lt;b&gt;local minimum&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;From feature \(A\), no matter what direction we move in we always loose height. Hence, \(A\) is a &lt;b&gt;local maximum&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;From feature \(B\), depending on the direction we move in we can either gain or loose height. Hence, \(B\) is a &lt;b&gt;saddle point&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
